text: Manfred Haake (born 9 November 1943) is a German rower who represented East Germany. He competed at the 1968 Summer Olympics in Mexico City in the men's double sculls with Uli Schmied where they came fifth. ==References== Category:1943 births Category:Living people Category:People from Spree-Neiße Category:People from the Province of Brandenburg Category:German male rowers Category:Sportspeople from Brandenburg Category:Olympic rowers of East Germany Category:Rowers at the 1968 Summer Olympics Category:World Rowing Championships medalists for East Germany Category:European Rowing Championships medalists
